  "prompt": "05 Tacoma 4 cylinder has slight vibration while stopped at a light, why?",
  "response": "There are several potential reasons for a vibration in a 2005 Toyota Tacoma 4-cylinder while stopped:\n\n1. Engine Mounts\n- Worn or damaged engine mounts can cause vibration\n- Rubber mounts deteriorate over time and allow more engine movement\n\n2. Spark Plugs\n- Worn or fouled spark plugs can cause uneven firing\n- Can create rough idle and vibration\n\n3. Idle Air Control Valve (IACV)\n- Dirty or malfunctioning IACV can cause irregular idle\n- Prevents smooth engine operation at idle\n\n4. Fuel System Issues\n- Clogged fuel injectors\n- Weak fuel pump\n- Dirty fuel filter\n\n5. Vacuum Leaks\n- Can cause uneven idle and vibration\n- Typically requires inspection of vacuum hoses and connections\n\n6. Motor Mounts\n- Worn or broken motor mounts can cause excessive engine movement\n\n7. Timing Belt/Chain Tension\n- Improper tension can cause engine vibration\n\nRecommended next steps:\n- Check and replace spark plugs\n- Inspect engine and motor mounts\n- Have a professional diagnostic scan\n- Check for vacuum leaks\n- Consider professional inspection if issue persists",
